Therefore, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the security of protocols in the context of communication networks, which could fall under cs.CE (Computers and Society) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
